### ===== STAGE 0: BASELINE DEMO =====

### 1. Process Payment (Valid Account)
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 2. Process Payment (Invalid Account)
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "INVALID-ACCOUNT",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### ===== STAGE 1: RETRY & CIRCUIT BREAKER =====
### (Enable GenericRandomErrorPlugin in devproxy.json first)

### 3. Test through DevProxy - Will retry on failures
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 75.50,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### ===== STAGE 2: OUTBOX PATTERN =====
### (UseOutbox: true in appsettings.Development.json)

### 4. Send payment - gets stored in outbox
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 200.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 5. Query outbox messages
GET http://localhost:5294/api/outbox

### ===== STAGE 3: INBOX PATTERN (IDEMPOTENCY) =====
### (UseInbox: true in CoreBankAPI appsettings.Development.json)

### 6. Send transaction with idempotency key (first time)
POST http://localhost:5032/api/transactions/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "idempotencyKey": "demo-payment-001"
}

### 7. Send SAME transaction again - should return cached response
POST http://localhost:5032/api/transactions/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "idempotencyKey": "demo-payment-001"
}

### 8. Query inbox messages
GET http://localhost:5032/api/inbox

### ===== STAGE 4: MESSAGE ORDERING =====
### (UseOrdering: true in appsettings.Development.json)

### 9. Multiple payments from Account 1 (should process in order)
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 10. Account 1 payment #2
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL39RABO0300065264",
  "amount": 20.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 11. Account 1 payment #3
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "toAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "amount": 30.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 12. Multiple payments from Account 2 (processes in parallel with Account 1)
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "toAccount": "NL91ABNA0417164300",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 13. Account 2 payment #2
POST http://localhost:5294/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "NL20INGB0001234567",
  "toAccount": "NL39RABO0300065264",
  "amount": 60.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 14. Check outbox to see partitions
GET http://localhost:5294/api/outbox

### ===== DIRECT CORE BANK API TESTS =====

